cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.LG, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the integration of computational cognitive models into robotics planning and control. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of mathematical models of human cognition in robot planning. 
3. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is relevant as the paper focuses on robots interacting with people and the need to plan with models of cognition. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of game-theoretic formulations and approximations in robot coordination behaviors. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also relevant as the paper discusses the planning and control of robots interacting with people.
